List-ID: <linux-kernel.vger.kernel.org>
X-Mailing-List: linux-kernel@vger.kernel.org
X-Lkml-Link: https://lkml.org/lkml/2000/3/24/215

Very simple:
ln -s foo foo
ls -lF foo
hangs, hit ^C, then watch the oopses scroll. This is on sparc64, IDE
system, ext2 filesystem. Reproducable everytime. Sorry I can't get you any
oops reports, but it scrolled by so fast that it pretty much tied my
system up (framebuffer never relinquished control, not even for a stop-a
or sysrq).
Ben
